news.title: Karnataka leader K J George's son Rana George buys flat for Rs 35 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: The deal was registered on April 19 and a stamp duty of around Rs 2 crore was paid as per the registry document shared by ZapKey. The luxury project is a joint venture with UB Group of Vijay Mallya and Prestige Group that holds a 45% interest in this Rs 1,300 crore project. Each flat is spread over 8,000 sft and prices start at around Rs 42,000 per sq. ft.

news.title: ABIL group chairman sent to CBI custody till June 8 by court in graft case
news.para: ​​Bhosale was arrested on Thursday (May 26) by the central probe agency, which suspects illicit funds were routed through several real estate firms based in Maharashtra.

news.title: Complete tenant verification or face action: Goa chief minister
news.para: “Police has started tenant verification in Goa. Those house owners who have not completed tenant verification will be fined. I urge the people to complete tenant verification,” Sawant said.

news.title: NGT sets aside EC for Young Builders' group housing near DU metro station
news.para: The tribunal was hearing a plea filed by the university against the grant of the EC by the Ministry of Environment and Forests for the construction of group housing with a built-up area of 1,37,879.64 sq meter at 1, 3 Cavalry Lane and 4 Chhatra Marg near the Vishwavidyalaya metro station by Young Builders Private Limited.

news.title: Rental housing searches in 13 cities grew 15.8% in Jan-Mar quarter: Report
news.para: Magicbricks.com is owned by Magicbricks Realty Services, which is a subsidiary of Times Internet.

news.title: Chennai corporation to create GIS database to map buildings, check violations
news.para: The corporation has finished mapping 190 of the 200 wards using drones, satellite images and field visits and gathered geographical info such as building details, size in 3D image, permission and owner details.

news.title: Noida: Residents file police complaint over fires at electrical panels
news.para: On Saturday, at 12 am, residents claimed to have averted an incident of fire in the electrical board of Tower D by calling an electrician to the complex after smelling burning wires and switching off the main electricity connection.

news.title: No piped drinking water in 72% homes in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: In the state, only 28.1% households have piped water as a source of drinking to their dwelling/plot/yard, showed survey. The piped water access as a source of drinking is not uniform across states because of a 32% gap in urban and rural areas.

news.title: Hyderabad: Discom pulled up for back billing, told to adjust Rs 1.7 lakh
news.para: A forum bench comprising chairperson N Jaya Raj and three members also directed the discom officials to adjust Rs 1.77 lakh excess bill in future bills if already collected from the villa owners, besides reversing their power connection to their previous LT-II category from the current LT-VIII category.

news.title: Three months to bring 10,000 commercial properties under tax net: Nashik municipal commissioner
news.para: These commercial properties are being used without obtaining building completion certificates (BCCs) from Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC).

news.title: Gurugram RWAs ask Haryana CM for legal recognition
news.para: They argued that some resident associations have proven very effective in managing local issues and supporting administrations in better management of the city.

news.title: Maharashtra housing societies 'lax' about fire safety
news.para: The housing societies need to submit the maintenance certificate in the form of "Form B" issued by the licensed agency stating that all fire protection systems are maintained and in a good working condition.

news.title: Gurugram civic body's takeover of DLF Phase 1-3 unlikely today
news.para: The civic body, TOI has learnt, is yet to calculate and hire manpower required for maintenance work and issue tenders for water and sewage services of the colonies. Without these, a takeover is not possible.

news.title: Chennai: After building plan approval goes online, number of applications up
news.para: While the online portal coinciding with the picking up of construction market is cited a reason for the hike in applications and the stakeholders gave a thumbs up for easing the application process, they said that the approval format has not changed.

news.title: Vipul's net loss widens to Rs 14.03 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: The company's total consolidated revenue stood at Rs 31.64 crore in Q4 FY22, a growth of 44.81 per cent from Rs 21.85 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
